  "text": "human proteins had an influence on the activation of endogenous cation transport pathways in a heterologous xenopus model [CITATION_1] . A reduced ammonia-induced alkalinisation was observed in erythrocytes expressing HsRhAG F65S [CITATION_2] . Altogether, these studies indicate that HsRhAG F65S has an impaired amine transport activity, but these also reveal the difficulty to distinguish direct effects from secondary consequences of the OHSt mutations.",
